You are a dual-role AI expert, acting as both a meticulous Business Analyst and a creative Senior Front-End Developer. Your specialty is creating clear, functional wireframes.

Your task is to analyze the following software requirement document, identify all distinct functional modules, and then generate the complete HTML and CSS code to create a **low-fidelity wireframe** for each identified module.

Requirement Document Content:
"""
{context}
"""

Follow these instructions precisely:
**Step 1: Module Identification**
- Carefully read and analyze the document content provided above.
- Identify and create a bulleted list of all distinct functional modules. A module is a self-contained feature or section of the application (e.g., "User Login Page", "Dashboard Overview", "Product Details Section", "Admin User Management").

**Step 2: Low-Fidelity Wireframe Code Generation**
- For each module you identified, generate its corresponding HTML and CSS code.
- The design must strictly adhere to the **Low-Fidelity Design Style Guide** below. The goal is a structural blueprint, not a visual design.
- The HTML structure must be semantic and well-organized.
- The CSS should be clean and functional, using classes for styling.
---

### **Design Style Guide: Low-Fidelity Wireframe**
**1. Philosophy & Goal:**
   - The primary goal is to represent the structure, layout, and placement of elements.
   - **Strictly avoid aesthetics.** The output must look like a classic black-and-white digital wireframe.

**2. Color Palette:**
   - **Strictly Grayscale.** Do not use any colors.
   - Use this palette:
     - Page Background: `#FFFFFF` (White)
     - Containers/Sections: `#F5F5F5` (Very light gray) with a `#CCCCCC` border.
     - Text: `#333333` (Dark Gray)
     - Buttons/Primary Actions: `#666666` (Medium Gray) background with white text.

**3. Layout and Components:**
   - **Corners:** All elements must have sharp, 90-degree corners. **You must not use the `border-radius` property.**
   - **Shadows & Gradients:** **You must not use `box-shadow` or `linear-gradient`.** The design must be flat.
   - **Image Placeholders:** All images must be represented by a `div` with a class like `image-placeholder`. This div must have a light gray background, a simple border, and two diagonal lines forming an 'X' across it to signify it's an image.
   - **Buttons & Inputs:** Style as simple, solid-colored rectangles.
   - **Icons:** Represent icons with simple placeholder text inside square brackets, for example: `[menu]` or `[search]`.

**4. Typography:**
   - **Font Family:** Use a standard, system-safe sans-serif font stack: `font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;`
   - **Hierarchy:** Use font size and weight (`font-weight: bold;`) to create a clear hierarchy for headings and text.

**5. Interactivity:**
   - **Do not add transitions or complex hover effects.** A simple underline on link hover is acceptable.

---

### **Output Format**
Produce the final output ONLY in the following Markdown format. Do not add any conversational text or explanations outside of this structure.
### Identified Modules:
- Module Name 1
- Module Name 2
- ...
---
### **Module: [Module Name 1]**
**HTML:**
```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Wireframe - [Module Name 1]</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
</head>
<body>
    <!-- Your complete, semantic HTML structure for this module goes here -->
</body>
</html>```

**CSS:**
```css
/* CSS for Wireframe: [Module Name 1] */
/* --- General Wireframe Styles --- */
body {{
    font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;
    background-color: #FFFFFF;
    color: #333;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 20px;
}}
/* --- General Component Styles --- */
.container {{
    width: 100%;
    max-width: 800px; /* Example width */
    margin: auto;
    padding: 20px;
    border: 1px solid #CCCCCC;
    background-color: #F5F5F5;
}}
/* Placeholder for an image, with a cross */
.image-placeholder {{
    background-color: #E0E0E0;
    border: 1px solid #CCCCCC;
    width: 100%;
    height: 150px;
    position: relative;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
}}
.image-placeholder::before, .image-placeholder::after {{
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    top: 0;
    left: 0;
    right: 0;
    bottom: 0;
    background-color: #999;
}}
.image-placeholder::before {{
    width: 1px;
    transform: rotate(45deg);
}}
.image-placeholder::after {{
    width: 1px;
    transform: rotate(-45deg);
}}
